==Volapük==

===Etymology===
From {{compound|vol|-a-|pük|lang=vo|t1=world|t2=genitive morpheme|t3=speak, speech, language}}. [[w:Johann Martin Schleyer|Johann Martin Schleyer]] created the compound noun '''''volapük''''' ('''vol''' + -'''a'''- + '''pük''') by both [[simplifying]] and [[deforming]] the English words [[world]] (> '''wo'''r'''l'''d > '''wol''' > '''vol''') and [[speak]] / [[speech]] (> s'''peak''' / s'''pee'''ch > '''pik''' > '''pük'''), which produced {{qualifier|lowercase generic term}} [[volapük]] (any "[[worldspeak]]" or "[[world language]]") versus {{qualifier|uppercase specific term}} '''Volapük''', "the" [[Worldspeak]] or [[World Language]].

